SOURCE: https://www.malarenergi.se//kundcenter-privat/information-in-other-languages/english/job-vacancies/thesis-project/
Apply with your own proposal
However, you can also submit your own proposal for thesis project via the form below. You describe the area you’re interested in, and then we run this by the relevant departments or functions within the business. Naturally, we would like to take on all applicants, but unfortunately this is not possible.
Time for your thesis work?
In order for us to proceed with your proposal, it’s important that you describe it in as much detail as possible. See it as an opportunity to sell your idea to us. Please also send in your CV and a personal letter.
If you want to conduct your thesis project with us, there are two ways of going about it. You can either apply for one of our advertised proposals for thesis projects, which we publish here on an ongoing basis. Since our thesis projects are based on the needs of the business, this is how we make most of the appointments.
In order to apply, you need to register your CV and application in our recruitment tool. Each ad contains information on the deadline for applications and when you can expect to receive a response from us. The ad also provides contact details for the tutor of the thesis project.
Utannonserade exjobb
Apply for published thesis projects
How does it work? | Mälarenergi
How does it work?


SOURCE: https://www.malarenergi.se//kundcenter-privat/information-in-other-languages/english/about-your-bill/
Direct debit means that the full bill amount is automatically taken from your bank account on the due date. To set up a direct debit, complete this mandate form:
Paper bill
E-billing means that an electronic (PDF) bill is sent and paid via your online banking service. It is a simple and secure payment method that reduces the environmental footprint. You apply for e-billing via your online banking service. Remember that the electricity account holder is the person who needs to make the application. Once you have applied for e-billing at your bank we will be notified of this and we will then change your account payment method to e-billing.
Your bill is divided into several different sections. They are each explained below.
Download example bill in English as pdf-document
Sign up for e-mail bill.
E-billing
Choose how you want to receive your bill
In exceptional circumstances when payment is not made despite reminders and debt collection demands we may have to resort to turning off your electricity.
Direct debit
You can manually pay your bill from your Internet Bank. Or you can use E-billing mentioned above. Or you can sign up for Direct debit.
E-mail bill
What happens if I don’t pay on time?
This means that you will receive your bill attached to an e-mail instead of a paper bill.
Choose how you want to pay
A reminder will be sent to you if you miss a payment. A reminder fee of SEK 60 and penalty interest will then be charged.
https://www.mvh.bgonline.se/Public.Web/Templates/MandateApplications/FillInMandateApplication.aspx?formRef=7e16405f-b066-4f75-b9e8-f178cc681541
Unless you request otherwise, you will receive a paper bill by post. You pay this at your bank no later than the due date.
If you have made late payments more than once in the current year, we will send a debt collection demand straight away without sending a reminder first.
If you still don’t pay despite the reminder, a debt collection demand will be sent and this will result in additional costs.
Bill invoice Mälarenergi | Mälarenergi


